HEADWORD: Coindication
<hw>Co*in`di*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>co⟦ium⟧dication</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of several signs or symptoms
indicating the same fact; <as>as, a <ex>coindication</ex> of
disease</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

